<br>
The haste cap for warriors (and all melees) works like this:<br>
Level 1-50: 70%<br>
Level 51-59: 85%<br>
Level 60: 100%<br>
<br>
It always has those values, there is no slow progression from level to level.<br>
<br>
I had the same idea as you though, I expected to see a 70% haste cap on the pets since they are lower than level 51.  Apparently the pets follow a different rule from PC's. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uhowwl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Howwl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(6/20/02 7:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1327.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Haste cap - Part III - Summary </span><hr size=1> One thing I feel compelled to point out... it may only be semantics, but it's important to remember when discussing things like this.<br>
<br>
With player characters anyway, there is no such thing as minimum delay.  I.e. there isn't a a lowest delay any particular weapon can be hasted to.  PC haste is capped at a percentage (roughly 100% for melee types at level 60).  But there is no minimum delay per weapon.<br>
<br>
Also, keep in mind that haste is a measure of increased attacks.  I.e. 100% haste makes you attack twice as fast.  It doesn't reduce your delay to zero.  100% haste would reduce an 18 delay weapon to a 9 delay weapon.<br>
<br>
Just FYI...<br>
<br>
So your 19 delay might be with a certain pet with certain weapons, but the delay might be different with a different pet or different weapons (i.e. the cap is the percentage, not the delay). <p><A HREF="http://interealms.com/profiles/profile.cfm?ID=6964">Howwl ShadowStalker</A> - Warder of The Glade<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.relicsguild.com">< Relics ></A>, Mithaniel Marr<br>
